+## Phase 6: AI Opponents
+
+**Goal:** 3 CPU opponents that race competently, use items, drift, and respond to difficulty per spec §8.
+
+**Files created:** `js/ai/aiDriver.js`, `js/ai/racingSplines.js`
+
+### 6.1 `js/ai/racingSplines.js`
+
+Per track, define:
+- **Center line:** Same as track center spline
+- **Optimal racing line:** Wide entry → tight apex → early exit on turns. Defined as a second CatmullRom spline with offset control points.
+- **3 variation splines:** ±2-4u lateral offsets from racing line (narrow ±1u on Crystal Caverns bridge). Each CPU picks random variation per lap for natural spacing.
+- **Drift zone markers:** `{ startT, endT, direction }` — zones where AI should drift
+  - Sunset: Hairpin (mandatory), S-curve entry (Standard/Mean only)
+  - Caverns: Lava Canyon (mandatory), Spiral Descent (mandatory), Crossover exit (Mean only)
+- **Hazard zones:** Spline ranges + lateral avoidance offsets (tunnel rocks, lava margin, crystal spikes, puddles)
+
+Precomputed arc-length parameterization for constant-speed traversal.
+
+Export: `getAITargetPoint(trackId, splineIndex, t)`, `isInDriftZone(trackId, t)`, `getHazardAvoidance(trackId, t)`
+
+### 6.2 `js/ai/aiDriver.js`
+
+**AI state per CPU:**
+```js
+{
+  character, difficulty, splineT, currentSplineIndex, variationIndex,
+  driftState, itemHoldTimer, overtakeState, personality
+}
+```
+
+**`updateAIDriver(ai, kartState, allKarts, trackData, activeItems, dt)`:**
+
+1. **Spline following (pure pursuit):**
+   - Compute current t from kart XZ position
+   - Look ahead by `lookaheadDist` (scales with speed, base 10-15u)
+   - Sample target point on current variation spline at `t + lookaheadT`
+   - Steer toward target (proportional + derivative controller for smooth turning)
+
+2. **Speed control:**
+   - Default: full acceleration
+   - Before tight curves (drift zones): ease off to 70% speed unless planning drift
+   - Difficulty speed scaling:
+     - Chill: 85-92% of character max
+     - Standard: 93-98%
+     - Mean: 98-102% (slight cheat boost)
+
+3. **Drift logic (spec §8.3):**
+   - In drift zone AND speed > threshold → initiate drift (same state machine as player, driven by synthetic input)
+   - Hold duration by difficulty:
+     - Chill: Tier 1 (0.6-0.8s), often cancels early
+     - Standard: Tier 2 (1.2-1.5s)
+     - Mean: Tier 3 (2.0-2.2s), consistent
+   - **Personality modifiers:**
+     - Brix: drifts rarely (low handling makes it risky), prefers braking into corners
+     - Zippy: drifts frequently, chains boosts
+     - Chunk: drifts when track demands it, doesn't chase risky boosts
+     - Pixel: drifts at every opportunity, consistently hits Tier 2-3
+
+4. **Item usage (spec §8.2):**
+   - **Aggressive (Brix, Pixel):** Offensive items immediately when target in range. Fires Spark Bomb ASAP with target ahead.
+   - **Item-Focused (Zippy):** Holds defensive items in 1st, hoards offensive until close (20u). Slightly deviates toward item boxes (±2u from racing line).
+   - **Defensive (Chunk):** Holds items as protection, uses reactively.
+   - **Difficulty modifies timing:** Chill: 1-3s lag. Standard: 0.5-1s lag. Mean: instant.
+   - Turbo Cell: all AIs use when not already boosting.
+
+5. **Hazard avoidance (spec §8.4):**
+   - Detect hazards within lookahead range, offset target point laterally
+   - Mean: 100% dodge. Standard: 85%. Chill: 60%.
+   - AI detects dropped Slick Puddles within 15u forward range, steers around
+
+6. **Overtaking (spec §8.5):**
+   - When AI is faster than kart ahead within 10u: attempt pass
+   - Pick side with more room (compare kart position to track center)
+   - Aggressive AI: will bump. Defensive AI: waits.
+
+7. **Rubber banding (spec §8.6):**
+   - Chill: +5% speed if >40u behind leader, -5% if >40u ahead of player
+   - Mean: +3% speed if >40u behind leader (catch-up only)
+   - Standard: none
+
+8. **Per-lap variation:** Random variation spline index at lap start to prevent bunching
+
+### 6.3 Validation Gate
+Start race → 3 CPUs drive the track, complete laps, drift at corners, collect and use items. Chill is beatable. Mean is very fast and aggressive. Position tracking is correct with AI. AI avoids hazards, drifts at designated zones, uses items per personality.
+
