+- Contact: immediate respawn at last checkpoint, +1.5s time penalty
+
+**Bridge edges (Crystal Caverns):**
+- No wall meshes on bridge section
+- Kart center outside bridge width → lava respawn
+
+### 8.4 Options Implementation
+
+**Mirror Mode:** Negate X-component of all track control points, AI spline points, hazard positions, scenery positions. Flip drift zone directions. Apply before geometry generation.
+
+**Allow Clones:** OFF = CPUs get remaining 3 unique characters. ON = each CPU picks randomly from all 4 (duplicates possible).
+
+### 8.5 Performance Optimization
+
+- Merge all static track geometry into minimal draw calls per section
+- `InstancedMesh` for: palm trees, crystals, mushrooms, item boxes
+- Object pool for particles (pre-allocated, show/hide)
+- Pre-allocate Vector3/Quaternion in hot loops (no `new THREE.Vector3()` in update)
+- Simple collision geometry separate from visual geometry
+- Frustum culling (built-in Three.js)
+- Target: < 100 draw calls/frame, 60fps on mid-range hardware
+- Graceful degradation: reduce particle count if frame time > 20ms; disable crystal point lights if still struggling
+
+### 8.6 Final Integration Checklist
+
+1. Title screen → track select → character select → difficulty → START
+2. Countdown with fly-over and beeps → "GO!"
+3. Racing: drive, drift, boost; items work; AI competes; HUD updates; minimap accurate
+4. Hazards: falling rocks, crystal spikes, lava kills, bridge falls
+5. Lap tracking: 3 laps, checkpoints prevent cutting, "FINAL LAP!" banner
+6. Position tracking: smooth 1st-4th updates
+7. Finish: overlay, camera change, CPUs finish, results screen
+8. Pause: Escape → resume/restart/quit
+9. Audio: engine, drift, boost, items, collisions, countdown, music per track
+10. Respawn: bridge fall, lava, stuck → checkpoint with invincibility
+11. All 4 characters with distinct visuals and noticeable stat differences
+12. Particles: drift sparks, boost flame, dust, explosions, confetti
+13. Performance: 60fps, <100 draw calls
+14. Test hooks: `render_game_to_text()` and `advanceTime()` return correct data
+15. Static deployment: serve `output/` → game loads and plays with no build step
+16. Both tracks fully functional with all hazards and shortcuts
+17. Mirror mode and clone toggle working
