+## Key Technical Decisions
+
+1. **Geometry merging:** All voxel karts and static track sections merged into single `BufferGeometry` objects with vertex colors. Manual merge implementation (accumulate float arrays, no Three.js addon dependency). Keeps draw calls under 100.
+
+2. **Collision system:** 2D XZ plane. Track walls = line segments. Karts = spheres (radius 1.5). Items = spheres/circles. Y-axis only for elevation and visual. Simple and fast.
+
+3. **Off-road detection:** Road is the spline-extruded ribbon. Point-to-spline-distance check: find closest spline t, compare XZ distance to half-width. Additional tagged surface zone polygons for sand/lava. O(log n) with precomputed lookup.
+
+4. **Spline representation:** `THREE.CatmullRomCurve3` for all centerlines and racing lines. Parametric t ∈ [0,1] maps to full lap. `getPointAt(t)` for position, `getTangentAt(t)` for direction.
+
+5. **AI steering:** Pure pursuit — target a point on the spline at `t + lookahead`. Proportional + derivative controller for smooth turning. Difficulty modifies speed caps, drift hold durations, dodge rates. No pathfinding.
+
+6. **AI uses same physics:** CPU karts run through the exact same physics pipeline as the player. AI generates synthetic input. Only differences are difficulty speed multipliers and rubber banding.
+
+7. **Audio autoplay:** `AudioContext` created on first user interaction only. All audio functions check context existence before playing.
+
+8. **No external assets:** Flat-color `MeshLambertMaterial` with vertex colors. Sky = colored background or gradient sphere. HUD icons = CSS-styled divs with Unicode. No PNG, OBJ, or MP3 files.
+
+9. **Import map:** Single CDN dependency: `"three"` → Three.js r160 module build. All internal imports use relative paths.
+
+10. **Frame-rate independence:** Every calculation uses `dt`. Clamped to max 1/30s to prevent physics explosion on tab-away.
+
+11. **Memory:** Particle pool fixed at 200. Items have finite lifetimes. No unbounded arrays. Pre-allocate Vector3 in hot loops.
+
+12. **CSS in separate file:** All styling in `css/style.css` rather than inlined, keeping `index.html` minimal and styles maintainable.
